OL,7,FWages and benefits in the UK may seem
OL,8,Fhigh on paper, but NIESR has compared
OL,9,Fdisposable incomes and made
OL,10,Fadjustments for purchasing power -
OL,11,Fwhich takes into account what people
OL,12,Fcan actually buy for their money.
OL,14,FThe conclusion is blunt:
OL,16,FThe lowest 10% of earners in the UK -
OL,17,Froughly three million households - are
OL,18,Fmore than #3000 a year worse off than
OL,19,Fthe poorest households in Germany and
OL,20,F#1500 a year worse off than the lowest
OL,21,Fearners in France.
